---
import DocPage from "../../../components/DocPage.astro"
const cb = "bg-background-dark p-3 border-l-2 border-border text-foreground-dark text-xs mb-6 overflow-x-auto"
---

<DocPage title="State Synchronization">
  <h1>State Synchronization</h1>

  <p>
    Shannon keeps your environment variables and working directory in sync
    across mode switches.
  </p>

  <h2>Environment Variables</h2>

  <pre class={cb}><code><span class="text-accent">[bash]</span> ~/project &gt; <span class="text-accent">export</span> <span class="text-warning">API_KEY</span>=<span class="text-success">"sk-1234"</span>
<span class="text-accent">[bash]</span> ~/project &gt; &lt;Shift+Tab&gt;
<span class="text-success">[nu]</span> ~/project &gt; <span class="text-warning">$env</span>.API_KEY
sk-1234</code></pre>

  <p>It works both ways:</p>

  <pre class={cb}><code><span class="text-success">[nu]</span> ~/project &gt; <span class="text-warning">$env</span>.FOO = <span class="text-success">"hello"</span>
<span class="text-success">[nu]</span> ~/project &gt; &lt;Shift+Tab&gt;
<span class="text-accent">[bash]</span> ~/project &gt; echo <span class="text-warning">$FOO</span>
hello</code></pre>

  <h2>Typed Value Conversion</h2>

  <p>
    Nushell stores some env vars as typed values (PATH is a list, not a string).
    Shannon handles this automatically:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Nu to Bash:</strong> <code class="text-secondary">env_to_strings()</code>
      converts typed values to strings using <code class="text-secondary">ENV_CONVERSIONS</code>
      <code class="text-secondary">to_string</code> closures
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Bash to Nu:</strong> String env vars are written back. Nushell automatically
      applies <code class="text-secondary">from_string</code> conversions on the next REPL iteration
    </li>
  </ul>

  <p>You don't need to do anything — PATH, LS_COLORS, and other typed vars just work.</p>

  <h2>Working Directory</h2>

  <pre class={cb}><code><span class="text-accent">[bash]</span> ~/project &gt; cd /tmp
<span class="text-accent">[bash]</span> /tmp &gt; &lt;Shift+Tab&gt;
<span class="text-success">[nu]</span> /tmp &gt;</code></pre>

  <h2>The Strings-Only Boundary</h2>

  <p>
    Only exported environment variables and the cwd cross between modes.
    Internal shell state does not transfer:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Nushell variables (<code class="text-secondary">let x = 5</code>) stay in nushell</li>
    <li>Bash local variables and aliases stay in bash</li>
    <li>Use <code class="text-secondary">export</code> / <code class="text-secondary">$env.X = ...</code> for values that need to cross</li>
  </ul>
</DocPage>
